        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section id="introduction" class="mb-24 text-center">
            <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black mb-4 tracking-tight">Project Chimera</h1>
            <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-600 mb-8">A Theoretical Framework for the Biophysics of Ascension</h2>
            <p class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-lg leading-relaxed">
                This report presents a speculative, interdisciplinary framework for understanding the phenomenon of "ascension" as a biophysical process. Moving beyond mythological or purely metaphysical interpretations, <strong>Project Chimera</strong> hypothesizes that ascension represents a quantifiable state-transition of a biological organism, from a baseline human state governed by classical biochemistry to a "divine" state characterized by macroscopic quantum coherence.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Part I -->
        <section id="part1" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold border-b-2 border-accent-color pb-2 mb-8">Part I: The Spectrum of Being - The Quantum Biological Model</h2>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="content-card p-6">
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">The central premise of this investigation is that the human body is not merely a biochemical machine but a complex quantum coherent system. The "spectrum of being" describes the range of functional states available to this system, with the baseline human at one end and the fully actualized <strong>Corpus Divinum</strong> at the other. The conventional biochemical model is insufficient to explain anomalous phenomena, while a Quantum Biological Model (QBM) provides a more robust framework.</p>
                </div>
